##Reunited, but with no end in sight

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhu Yuanxiang is a reporter for the paper

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the night of March 6, Shen Junliang arrived in Zengcheng from Jinan. Zhu Yuanxiang, reporter, thepaper.cn

On the night of March 7, Shen Junliang finally met his son, who had been abducted for 15 years.

Fifteen years ago, Shen Junliang's son Shen Cong was just a one-year-old baby. Now he is a 1.7-meter-tall boy. He is a junior in a township middle school in Guangdong, health, Sunshine, love to play basketball. For more than a decade, he didn't even know he was a child.

"From now on, I will make it up to him and make up for the love I owe him for 15 years, " Shin told The Paper. The gifts he got his son for the meeting included a new sportswear outfit from the inside out, as well as five N95 masks.

The recognition of relatives, whether it means that Shen Cong was abducted a matter of closure? Shin Junliang doesn't think so. On the one hand, there are still many practical issues to be resolved as to which side Shen Cong will live on in the future and how to handle the relationship between his biological parents and his adoptive parents. On the other hand, Shen Junliang feels that the case of his son's abduction has not yet been decided with a hammer, "Only when all the people who abducted and sold my son are severely punished and Mei Yi is caught will this matter be brought to a satisfactory conclusion. "

However, Shenjunliang identified as an important intermediary trafficking case "Meiyi" , the real identity of who? It's still a mystery.

"This time it's 100% . "

The police found this happy news of Shen Cong, Shen Junliang was in 2020 on the eve of the Spring Festival.

It was January 15, and police officers from the new town police station of the Tianqiao Branch of the Jinan Public Security Bureau called him to find out where he lived and to verify whether he had provided DNA information for the search for his son. Shen Junliang only after the call, immediately called the Guangzhou Public Security Bureau Zengcheng district police, confirmed the "great happy event" —— Son Shen Cong found, DNA match information!

Shin immediately called The Paper, a journalist. "I'm so excited. I can't stand, I can't sit. " Shin, almost choked with emotion, kept punching the mattress beside him with his cellphone in one hand and his hand in the other. "maybe a few hundred times, " he laughed. "I don't know if it's pleasure or Catharsis. "

In that "Annunciation" of the call, Shen Junliang stressed: "This is really 100% , not false. "

Over the past decade, Shen Junliang because "found son" such news, empty joy many times.

Born in 1977, Shen Junliang is from Zhoukou, Henan Province. In 2005 he worked as a factory worker in Zengcheng, Guangzhou, where he lived with his wife and son, Shen Cong. Shin was robbed on January 4 of that year. Police later confirmed that two men took advantage of Shen Junliang's absence that day, broke into his rented house, tied up his wife, and then forcibly took the one-year-old Shen Cong from his bed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A photo of Shin Cong before his first birthday

Because of the pain of losing a son, Shen Cong's mother once mental disorder, Shen Junliang is on the long road to find his son. He sold his family's property, went to Shandong relatives and friends, and raised money to find his son in Guangzhou, Dongguan, Zhuhai, Shenzhen and other places. Over Missing, he posted more than 800,000 copies and owed more than 500,000 yuan in debt.

Shen Junliang persisted for fifteen years in searching for his son with extraordinary perseverance. Sometimes he doesn't have a clue, doesn't know where to look, and puts his phone on the concrete and turns it around, as if it's pointing in the right direction.

In March 2016, five people, including Zhang Weiping and Zhou Rongping, were arrested by the police in connection with the abduction and trafficking of Shen Cong, which injected a "heart-strengthening agent" into the exhausted Shen Junliang. Zhang initially told police that he had sold him to the Xiang River Road area in Zengcheng. So Shen Junliang to Xiangjiang Road around the door-to-door search for a few months. The innkeeper of the hotel where he was staying took pity on him and reduced his daily rate from 80 yuan to 45 yuan.

One day, a female resident whispered to Shin that her best friend had bought a child in 2003, probably Shin Cong, at a middle school across the street from Shin's hotel. Thus Shen Junliang observed the boy as a tip -- A white-skinned, double-eyelid boy. "The age of the child and the time and place of the abduction match, I think it must be right, " said Shen, who gave information about the child to the police and spent his days climbing by the hotel window, looking for "Son" to go to school, after school when the figure. But it turned out that the kid wasn't Shin Cong.

In the summer of 2017, hope returned. "Human Trafficker" Zhang Weiping confessed that he sold Shen Cong to Zijin County, Heyuan. Therefore, the main battlefield where Shen Junliang searched for his son was located in Zijin.

In a town in Zijin County, he was told that a junior high school student had been "bought" by his family. He rented a van and parked at the school gate. "The child was thin with a face shaped like my younger brother's when he was a child, " Shen said, quietly taking a photo of the child and sending it to a well-known expert in mock-ups. "He said the similarity was 90 percent, " Shin said with conviction. For a while, an informant who helped him keep an eye on things reported to him every day, "your son has gone to school, " "your son just got out of school... " which made Shen Jun's conscience "itchy. ".

But then a DNA match came back, and the boy was ruled out. "I was so upset at the time, and I felt a lot of pain in my heart, " said Shen, who has kept his emotions in check since receiving similar news. "The more I hope, the more I will be disappointed. "

It wasn't until January 2020 that Shin's 15 year dream of finding his son finally came true.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shen Junliang looks through the Missing of his suitcase at his rented house in Jinan. Zhong Xiaomei, reporter, thepaper.cn

Inter-provincial kinship recognition, a special trip during the epidemic

On January 15, after hearing the news, Shen Junliang immediately asked the Zengcheng police in Guangzhou to take him home for the Spring Festival. He was warned that there were still many details to be worked out.

A week before the 2020 Spring Festival, police in Guangzhou rushed to Jinan, Shandong Province, to brief Shen on the progress of the case and discuss a plan to identify relatives.

Shen Junliang told The Paper that, according to the police, he was in the third year of his junior year at a township middle school, and had a sister and a brother who were both in school; his adoptive parents had been away working for years, and the family was not well off.

"I was a little sad, and I felt that Shen Cong didn't have a good life, " Shen said. Later, when the police comforted him, "the child was in good health, " he was relieved. Over the years, he had seen reports of children who had been abducted and had been worried about Shin's health.

Shen Junliang and the police to deal with the good, the first month after the seventh day of recognition in Guangdong pro. Then, he took his wife and two sons home to Henan New Year. Two Boys, 14 and 12. "They three brothers, happen to have a child every two years. " Shen Junliang smiles. After Shen Cong accident, someone said "Cong" homophonic "Chong" , is "two drops of water to the child rushed out of the home. Therefore, Shen Junliang named the children more exquisite, later the two sons' names, all carry a "home" word —— -- Foshan -- Shen Junliang hoped that they would take root in the home.

During the Spring Festival in his hometown in Henan Province, Shen found him and told some relatives and friends, but kept his 70-year-old mother in the dark. "My mother's character is more urgent than I am, " he said. "knowing this, I'm sure I can't sleep every night. She's not well. "

Shen said he was "very miserable" and "the time went by very slowly" during the Spring Festival this year. His plans to travel south to Guangdong have been repeatedly delayed by the severity of the new crown pneumonia outbreak.

At that time, he paid close attention to the epidemic in Guangdong every day, but also paid attention to the "QQ movement" with a police officer he was familiar with. If he sees her walking more than 10,000 steps on any given day, he immediately texts her, asking if she's "on the move" -- as if she went to see Shen and his adoptive parents?

At 9 p.m. on March 5, Shen Junliang, who had received information from the police, set off immediately. Before leaving home, he has rented a room, bed board, desk clean, as the bedroom and study after Shen Cong home.

Shen Junliang took his wife and brother and drove his brother's car from Jinan to Guangzhou. On the way, the trio are in high spirits, debating whether to take their children to Thousand Buddha Mountain or to Baotu spring before heading back to Florida?

Shen Junliang drove very fast. "I always feel like I'm going too slow, and I want to get there in a hurry, " he says, remembering the "serious overspeed" warning in his navigation voice, "and before I knew it, I was on the gas. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shen Junliang was interviewed by the paper after arriving in Guangzhou on March 6. Zhu Yuanxiang, reporter, thepaper.cn

At 8 p.m. on March 6, Shen and his entourage arrived in Zengcheng district of Guangzhou City. The more than 1,800 km journey took them just 23 hours -- an all night drive to Florida, hungry for instant noodles. When Shen arrived in Zengcheng for a 20-hour drive to meet the paper's reporter, wearing a mask, he was so tired that he could barely straighten his back.

That night, Shen Junliang line in the public security police arrangements, overnight to the hospital for nucleic acid testing, to ensure that no infection of new pneumonia.

While Shen and his wife were being tested at the hospital, the Guangzhou police issued a notice overnight saying that the public security authorities had found Shen's abducted son in Meizhou, Guangdong, and that they would follow the relevant regulations for the prevention and control of the epidemic, to organize the identification of the next of kin while ensuring safety.

Meeting after 15 years: Anticipation and fear

On the first night after a 20-hour drive to Guangzhou, Shen stayed up almost all night.

Shortly after 10:00 that night, he posted a long, 1,000-word message on his wechat friends'circle. "I've thought about it for a long time but I don't know how to begin, or what words to use to describe my current mood, " he wrote at the beginning. "I have a happy announcement for you today. My son, Shen Cong, has been found! "

Shen Junliang in this long article, to investigate and supervise the case of Shen Cong police, leaders, as well as the news media and friends one by one to express gratitude. "I am proud to say that I am Shin Cong's father, and my son has been found, " he concluded

That night, Shin's cellphone was nearly "blown up, " and he was afraid to answer it. "There are more than 200 missed calls. " He was interviewed by the media over and over in his hotel room until dawn. Exhausted, but not too sleepy, he faced the media and talked endlessly about finding Satoshi. He dried out and took a drink of water. His Blue Mask was almost wet. His speech was punctuated by gestures, mood swings, glances and glances.

"I can't wait to meet Shen Cong. I haven't been around for 15 years, and I don't know what it will be like to meet him. I'm both looking forward to it and a little scared, " he told thepaper.cn, "I was afraid that Shen wouldn't take it in his heart, that he wouldn't want to be close to his family. I don't know if he would reject us because we were strangers. "

Shin's concerns are not groundless. In November 2019, police in Zengcheng, Guangzhou, found two other children who had been abducted for more than a decade and organized the identification of their biological parents. However, communication between the two parties has not been smooth since then and the children have not returned home with their biological parents.

But Shin believes his son will go home with him. He told the paper his "bottom line" -- that even if Shen Cong had to study and live in Guangdong for the exam, he would have to move his Hukou back to his hometown.

Early on the morning of March 7, a classmate of Shen Junliang arrived in Zengcheng from Dongguan, bringing Shen's purchases to him -- a set of clothes from a famous sports brand, including underwear, shoes and socks. This set of "from inside to outside" clothes cost about 2,000 yuan. It was a day before Shen Junliang prepared for his son to meet him. He just found out that Shen Cong was about 1.7 meters tall, neither fat nor thin. In addition, Shen Junliang also prepared for his son epidemic prevention of 5 N95 masks.

At noon that day, the Zengcheng district public security branch of the police will be a good couple of Shen Jun received Criminal Police Brigade. Hearing the news came to the country more than 50 reporters gathered at the door, waiting for the news of Shen Jun good recognition. According to the plan, Shin will meet with Shin and his adoptive parents.

On March 7, Shen Junliang was quoted by the media as saying that he had told the police that he strongly wanted to go home with his father, Shen Junliang. However, the lawyer has since denied it. Later that afternoon, Shin finally arrived at the door. He looked serious and said a few words of thanks to the media, and asked everyone not to take photos and announce Shin's personal image. He added that some of the statements made by his lawyer did not represent his views and those of his family. Finish saying, Shen Junliang is accompanied by a staff member to quickly walk into the courtyard.

Many reporters gathered in front of the Public Security Bureau felt at the time that Shen Junliang's family identification might not go well.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On March 7, Li Guangri, deputy director of the Zengcheng District Bureau of the Guangzhou Public Security Bureau, introduced the case.

Shortly after 5:00 p.m. that day, the Zengcheng District Bureau of the Guangzhou Municipal Public Security Bureau held a briefing. Deputy Director Li Guangri to the media, Shen Junliang couple and Shen Cong have not met to recognize the pro. "We haven't met yet, not at the moment, but we will arrange it, " Li said, adding that the two sides need an emotional buffer to meet. As for when to arrange a meeting, "It depends on the acceptance of both sides. ".

Li said he had met 16-year-old Shen Cong and found him healthy and bright. "He hasn't expressed his desire to live on any side, " he said

By 10 pm on March 7, the press office of the Guangzhou Public Security Bureau announced that at about 19 pm tonight, the Zengcheng police had arranged for a reunion between Shen and his wife, who had been separated for 15 years, and their son, Shen.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Weiping's child abduction case involved nine children, including Shen Cong. Some of the family members showed photographs of the abducted child as a child. Zhu Yuanxiang, reporter, thepaper.cn

"Aunt May" is still a mystery

On the evening of March 7, Shen Junliang stopped speaking to the media after he was introduced to his son, Shen Cong.

He had previously told The Paper news that he wanted a quiet family life once he got his children back. "after Shen Cong returns to his family, our family will make him happy and comfortable, " he said, adding that he would find a new job to live well and "create good conditions for the children. ".

However, Shen Junliang said that the abduction of his son can not be completely "ended. " "I hope that the people who abducted and sold my son will be severely punished, and that Meiyi will be arrested as soon as possible, so that I can return to my family with peace of mind and live a good life. "

Zhang Weiping and Zhou Rongping, who have been found guilty of abducting and selling Shen Cong, are all from Suiyang County, Guizhou Province, from the same village. They were sentenced by the Guangzhou Intermediate People's Court in December 2018 for the crime of abducting and selling children, zhang Weiping and Zhou Rongping were sentenced to death in the first trial.

The case has been appealed to the 廣東省高級人民法院 and is still pending. In the second trial, Shen Junliang and his wife continue to express the criminal incidental civil claims.

Shen was not the only child abducted and sold by the "human trafficker" , Zhang Weiping. The Guangzhou Intermediate Court found that between September 2003 and December 2005, Zhang Weiping was involved in the abduction and sale of nine children, including Shen Cong. Of the nine abducted boys, the youngest was one year old and the oldest three years old.

In November 2019, Guangzhou police recovered two abducted children whose biological parents were from Guizhou and Sichuan provinces.

"over the years, we have not given up looking for the nine abducted children, " Li Guangri, deputy director of the Zengcheng District Public Security Bureau, said at a briefing on March 7, "We are still working on finding the remaining six children, but we can not give you an expectation at the moment. "

And according to Zhang Weiping previously confessed, he abducts 9 children, it is through Middleman"Mei Yi"introduction, sell to Guangdong Zijin County and other places.

Who the hell is "aunt May" ? "She was about forty-five or six years old at the time, with short hair and a tendency to speak in Mandarin, " Zhang said at his 2017 court hearing in Guangzhou. He did not know her real name, but it was more than a decade ago when he rented a room in Zengcheng, the two old men next door introduced us.

Zengcheng police told The Paper news in November 2017 that police had taken Zhang to find the two elderly people who knew her. One of them has died and the other is suffering from dementia and Amnesia.

During the trial, prosecutors produced case file materials show that the police also took Zhang Weiping in Zijin County to find "Meiyi" of the former boyfriend. The man, surnamed Peng, said he had been in a relationship with a 50-year-old woman 12 years ago and had not been in contact six years ago. According to her, the woman's name is Fan Dongmei.

Can the police in the public security information network inquiries, did not find the relevant age range of "Fan Dongmei. ".

In June 2017, the Zengcheng District Bureau of the Guangzhou Public Security Bureau released a mock portrait of Meiyi to solicit clues from the community. The woman, nicknamed "Mei Yi" , has been involved in several trafficking cases. Her real name is unknown. She is about 65 years old, 1.5 meters tall, speaks Cantonese and Hakka people, and has long been active in Zengcheng and Xinfeng Shaoguan, the notice said.

At the briefing, Li Guangri said that since 2017, Guangzhou police have received "Meiyi" clues reported by the masses in many parts of the country, and have been checked one by one, have been excluded.

Li said the police had verified "almost all the details" of Zhang's statement, but still had not found the identity of "Mei Yi, " saying there was "no direct evidence to prove the existence of Mei Yi. "

"media friends and enthusiastic people are welcome to provide us with valuable clues, " Li said. "We will do our best to verify each one in a very responsible way. "
